= Installing the latest source code from the [[Git]] repository =

<pre lang="shell">$ git clone git://git.wincent.com/bansshee.git
$ cd bansshee
$ sudo make install</pre>

= Testing required dependencies =

<pre lang="shell">$ perl -c /usr/local/sbin/bansshee
Can't locate Proc/Daemon.pm in @INC
$ sudo -H cpan Proc::Daemon
$ perl -c /usr/local/sbin/bansshee 
Can't locate File/Tail.pm in @INC
$ sudo -H cpan File::Tail
$ perl -c /usr/local/sbin/bansshee 
/usr/local/sbin/bansshee syntax OK</pre>

= Setting up [[iptables]] =

First, customize firewall rules as desired (beyond the scope of this document) in `/etc/sysconfig/iptables`.

Start `iptables`:

<pre lang="shell">$ sudo service iptables start</pre>

Set up [[iptables]] to automatically launch at boot time:

<pre lang="shell">$ sudo chkconfig iptables on</pre>

